# Logs Directory

This directory stores application logs.

## Log Files

- `django_errors.log` - Django application errors and warnings
- Created automatically when the application runs with logging enabled

## Viewing Logs

### Local Development
```bash
# View recent errors
tail -50 logs/django_errors.log

# Monitor logs in real-time
tail -f logs/django_errors.log
```

### Sevalla Production
```bash
# View Passenger/Apache errors
tail -100 ~/logs/yourdomain.com/http/error.log

# Monitor in real-time
tail -f ~/logs/yourdomain.com/http/error.log
```

## Log Rotation

Logs may grow large over time. Consider implementing log rotation:

### Linux/Unix (logrotate)
Create `/etc/logrotate.d/string_analyzer`:
```
/path/to/string_analyzer/logs/*.log {
    daily
    rotate 14
    compress
    delaycompress
    notifempty
    missingok
}
```

### Manual Cleanup
```bash
# Archive old logs
gzip logs/django_errors.log

# Or delete old logs
rm logs/django_errors.log
```

## Note

This directory and `.gitkeep` file ensure the logs directory exists in version control without tracking log files themselves.
